    "body": "Installing packages that require a license file (seen with intel and pgi packages today) appear to hang forever after the license file is supplied interactively during installation. Re-starting installation with the license file already in place works.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ spack install pgi@19.4 %gcc@4.8.5\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Error Message\r\n\r\n```console\r\njoan5896  95984  95849  0 08:51 pts/25   00:00:00          \\_ python /curc/sw/spack-experimental/bin/spack install pgi@19.4 %gcc@4.8.5\r\njoan5896  96013  95984  5 08:51 pts/25   00:00:08              \\_ [vim] <defunct>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Information on your system\r\n\r\nRunning on RHEL7.6\r\n\r\nUsing spack develop, 3ce90741a3dd82b22139f82a555e0158c796c169",
